<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[818,1443,447,731]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis box="[818,952,447,467]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Notes: Alfaria</emphasis>
is a very morphologically distinct lineage among the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1895" box="[818,938,476,496]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Ectatommini">Ectatommini</taxonomicName>
, given the extreme anterior curvature of the gaster in profile. In fact, these ants are usually mistakenly identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Roger, 1863" authorityName="Roger" authorityYear="1863" box="[818,1051,535,555]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Proceratium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[818,931,536,554]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Proceratium</emphasis>
Roger, 1863
</taxonomicName>
, due to the impressive convergence in this character. We here resurrect the name 
<emphasis box="[1186,1250,564,584]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Alfaria</emphasis>
, firstly proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Emery, C." box="[818,949,593,613]" journalOrPublisher="Boll. Soc. Entomol. Ital." pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="33 - 107" part="28" refId="ref18436" refString="Emery, C. 1896. Studi sulle formiche della fauna neotropica. XVII-XXV. Boll. Soc. Entomol. Ital. 28: 33 - 107." title="Studi sulle formiche della fauna neotropica. XVII-XXV" type="journal article" year="1896">Emery (1896)</bibRefCitation>
and synonymized under 
<taxonomicName box="[1197,1336,594,613]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Gnamptogenys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1197,1336,594,613]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Gnamptogenys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Brown, W. L. Jr." journalOrPublisher="Bull. Mus. Comp. Zool." pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="173 - 362" part="118" refId="ref17913" refString="Brown, W. L. Jr. 1958. Contributions toward a reclassification of the Formicidae. II. The Ectatommini (Hymenoptera). Bull. Mus. Comp. Zool. 118 (5): 173 - 362." title="Contributions toward a reclassification of the Formicidae. II. The Ectatommini (Hymenoptera)" type="journal article" year="1958">Brown (1958)</bibRefCitation>
, to comprise the species previously included in the 
<emphasis box="[1377,1442,624,642]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">minuta</emphasis>
group of 
<taxonomicName authority="sensu Brandao and Lattke (1990)" authorityName="sensu Brandao and Lattke" authorityYear="1990" box="[915,1398,652,672]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Gnamptogenys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[915,1054,653,672]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Gnamptogenys</emphasis>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Brandao, C. R. F. &amp; J. E. Lattke" box="[1129,1398,652,672]" journalOrPublisher="J. N Y. Entomol. Soc." pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="489 - 494" part="98" refId="ref17742" refString="Brandao, C. R. F., and J. E. Lattke. 1990. Description of a new Ecuadorean Gnamptogenys species (Hymenoptera: Formicidae), with a discussion on the status of the Alfaria group. J. N Y. Entomol. Soc. 98: 489 - 494." title="Description of a new Ecuadorean Gnamptogenys species (Hymenoptera: Formicidae), with a discussion on the status of the Alfaria group." type="journal article" year="1990">Brandão and Lattke (1990)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. All 
<emphasis box="[818,882,681,701]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Alfaria</emphasis>
species can be identified using the work of Camacho et. al. (2020) under the previous combination in 
<emphasis box="[1209,1356,711,730]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Brandao and Lattke" authorityYear="1990" box="[1209,1352,711,730]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Gnamptogenys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Gnamptogenys</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
